<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Zend_Filter_Input::_validateRule() has the following code:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
/**
 * Evaluate the inputs against the validator chain.
 */
if (count((array) $validatorRule[self::FIELDS]) &gt; 1) {
    ....
} else {
    $failed = false;
    foreach ($data as $fieldKey =&gt; $field) {
        ....
    }
    ....
}
</code></pre>

<p>But $data cardinality is always less than (array) $validatorRule[self::FIELDS] cardinality since $data elements are collected by iterating through it.</p>

<p>It's not a bug, but it reduces code readability ($data is always one element array).</p>

